<TITLE> Aktel to share GP infra too </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 10 (bdnews24.com)  Aktel will be expanding its network by sharing infrastructure of Grameenphone Ltd, the country's largest mobile operator. A Memorandum of Understanding was signed between the two companies on Wednesday. Aktel, the third largest operator in Bangladesh, will be able to expand its network coverage through the sharing which in turn will reduce network costs for GP, a joint statement said. The companies said customers of both operators would benefit. Grameenphone and Banglalink, the number one and number two mobile operators, have signed similar infrastructure sharing agreement aimed minimising use of land and saving cost. Oddvar Hesjedal, chief executive officer of Grameenphone, said they had not yet decided on the amount of sharing. BTRC chairman Zia Ahmed has said the network sharing will be in line with the regulatory commission's directives. Currently six mobile companies operate in Bangladesh. b
